
[1]peroration

   PERORA'TION, n. [L. peroratio, from peroro; per and oro, to pray.]

   The concluding part of an oration, in which the speaker recapitulates
   the principal points of his discourse or argument, and urges them with
   greater earnestness and force,with a view to make a deep impression on
   his hearers.
